<br><br>
<strong>Is my collection or delivery date guaranteed?</strong>
<br><br>
Ensure collection dates. Certainly, we can! However, the auto-hauling industry only guarantees delivery dates due to the possibility of unforeseen events.
<br><br>
To determine the additional cost associated with meeting your deadline, you need only indicate whether you require the vehicle to be returned by a certain date or on a specific day. If you require specific collection dates, please get in touch with us for individualized quotes.
<br><br>
<strong>How do I get my vehicle ready for transport?</strong>
<br><br>
There are multiple methods to prepare your vehicle for auto transport:
<ul>
 	<li>Remove all personal items, including aftermarket electronics and accessories;</li>
 	<li>Ensure the interior and exterior of the vehicle are spotless. This will facilitate the transportation company's inspection of vehicles for pre-existing damage.</li>
 	<li>Inspect the fluid levels and inflate the tires to the proper pressure.</li>
 	<li>Confirm that the vehicle is operating well and has no fluid leaks.</li>
 	<li>If an alarm system is present, disable it.</li>
 	<li>Maintain roughly a quarter tank of gasoline in the vehicle.</li>
 	<li>Before transporting a vehicle, it must be photographed from all angles to document its condition.</li>
 	<li>Ensure you have all required documentation, including the vehicle's title and registration.</li>
 	<li>Notify the transportation company if the vehicle is inoperable so that they can make the appropriate arrangements.</li>
 	<li>Additional degassing fees will apply if you transport your vehicle to Alaska or Hawaii with more than a quarter tank of petroleum.</li>
</ul>
